content: I am a 4th-year Computer Science PhD student at UT Austin, co-advised by Işıl Dillig and Joydeep Biswas . I currently work on applying probabilistic program synthesis to robotics applications, and my past research has been mostly focusing on combining machine learning with programming language techniques and its application in programming languages and software engineering. Before joining UT, I received my bachelor’s degree in Physics from the University of Science and Technology of China.
